---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { GAME_NAME } from '../data/site';

const pageSourceIds = ['DB-SERP-001', 'DB-ROBLOX-001', 'DB-API-001'];
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Wiki Status"
  description="Demon Born wiki status — what the SERP actually shows and what is still missing."
  canonicalUrl="/wiki/"
  breadcrumb={[{ label: 'Wiki Status', url: '/wiki/' }]}
  evidenceNotes="SERP gap confirmed — no authoritative wiki hub found yet"
  sourceIds={pageSourceIds}
>
  <h1>{GAME_NAME} Wiki — Status</h1>

  <p class="page-lead">
    Is there a reliable {GAME_NAME} wiki? The current SERP is mixed —
    here is what actually exists and what is still missing.
  </p>

  <div class="info-block">
    <strong>Current status:</strong> No authoritative, official-source-backed wiki hub confirmed.
    An exact-match competitor (<em>demonbornwiki.wiki</em>) exists but its content has not been
    verified against official sources.
  </div>

  <h2>What the SERP shows (2026-06-27)</h2>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Result type</th>
          <th>Example</th>
          <th>Assessment</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Exact-match wiki</td>
          <td>demonbornwiki.wiki</td>
          <td>Exists but content unverified against official sources</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Unrelated Fandom results</td>
          <td>Fandom wikis for other games appearing for broad queries</td>
          <td>Not relevant to Demon Born</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Third-party guide sites</td>
          <td>Pocket Tactics, Destructoid, treyexgaming</td>
          <td>Code lists and beginner guides; not full wikis</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Reddit threads</td>
          <td>Community discussions</td>
          <td>Useful as leads only; not authoritative</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>YouTube videos</td>
          <td>Gameplay and guide videos</td>
          <td>Orientation only; not structured reference material</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>What official sources confirm</h2>
  <p>
    The Roblox Games API and official game page (source: <code>DB-API-001</code>) confirm:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Title: <strong>[WORLD CUP BETA] Demon Born</strong></li>
    <li>Creator: Roblox group <strong>SoraExp</strong></li>
    <li>Genre: Action RPG, RPG</li>
    <li>Description: open world with mysteries, challenging quests and demons</li>
    <li>Two player routes: become a slayer or embrace the dark side and fight to destroy humanity</li>
    <li>Controls: Left Click Attack, U Quest Indicators, Q Dash, F Defense, ALT Lock, SHIFT Run, B Finish, H Breathing, M Menu</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What is not yet confirmed</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Clan or class system details</li>
    <li>Breathing styles or blood demon arts mechanics</li>
    <li>Specific quest names, dungeon locations, or boss names</li>
    <li>Level progression or stat systems beyond the official description wording</li>
    <li>Active codes from an official Roblox or creator channel</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>This site as a wiki alternative</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Demon Born Compass</strong> tracks official source status and publishes only
    verified facts. It does not replace a full wiki — it fills the gap for the most
    common queries (controls, beginner facts, codes status) where reliable information
    is currently absent.
  </p>
  <p>
    As official sources are confirmed or gameplay testing becomes available,
    additional pages will be added within the <a href="/editorial/">editorial policy</a> boundaries.
  </p>

  <h2>Contribute</h2>
  <p>
    If you have verified official information about {GAME_NAME}, use the
    <a href="/contact/">correction workflow</a> to submit it.
    All additions require an official source before publication.
  </p>
</ContentLayout>